{
  "texts": [
    "Property 2 specifies a lower bound for the rank when matrices undergo addition.",
    "Property 3 constrains the rank of the product of two matrices to be bounded by the smaller of both.",
    "Property 4 states that square matrices that are invertible (for example, identity matrix I n) have a rank equal to the number of rows/columns (n).",
    "LoRA (Hu et al., 2022) updates a pre-trained weight matrix W 0 ∈ R d×k by additive update, i.e., h = W 0 x + ∆Wx, where x is the input and W 0 is frozen during fine-tuning.",
    "The updates ∆W are constrained to a low-rank decomposition BA where B ∈ R d×r, A ∈ R r×k and r ≪ min(d, k), i.e.,"
  ]
}